Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 425 degrees. Halve @eggplant{1} lengthwise, then cut into 1-inch-thick wedges. Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1} into ½-inch wedges. Toss eggplant and onion on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast in oven until browned, about ~{25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, put 1 1/2 cups water and a pinch of salt in a #small pot{} and bring to a boil. Once water is boiling, add @tri-colored quinoa{1/2%cup}. Reduce to a simmer and cover. Cook until quinoa is tender and water is absorbed, about ~{15%minutes}. Stir in @peas{4%oz} and remove from heat. Keep covered until rest of meal is ready.

Pick @mint{1/4%oz} leaves from stems. > Stems can be added to the quinoa for flavor. Discard before serving. Finely chop mint leaves until you have 1 TBSP. Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%oz} and its stems. Zest @Meyer lemon{1}, then squeeze juice into a #small bowl{}.

In another small bowl, whisk chopped mint, cilantro, half the lemon juice, a pinch of lemon zest, and @olive oil{2%tbsp}. Season with salt, pepper, and a pinch of @chili flakes{pinch}.

Add @sour cream{2%tbsp} and @water{2%tbsp} to the bowl with the remaining lemon juice and combine. Season with salt, pepper, and a pinch of remaining chili flakes.

Fluff quinoa with a #fork{}, then divide between plates. Top with eggplant and onion. Sprinkle with @feta cheese{1/2%cup}, then spoon crema and dressing on top.